"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"b28d6a",
"class":"cell txt li",
"children":[
"Axial involvement"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"35f24e",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Axial involvement is hallmark; initially symmetric involvement of SI joints and lower spine, progressing cranially"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"5793ae",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"May occur at any level; may start in the cervical spine; may skip regions"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"57ad6e",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"May have asymptomatic or asymmetric SI joint disease or have typical ankylosing spondylitis; axial disease does not parallel bowel activity"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"da94ab",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Less common than in other forms of spondyloarthritis but may be asymmetric"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-1 row-odd"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"eee2e1",
"class":"cell txt li",
"children":[
"Peripheral involvement"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"0ac9f8",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Enthesitis; may have asymmetric large-joint oligoarthritis, including hips and shoulders; hip involvement can cause significant functional limitation; dactylitis uncommon"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ff3439",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Clinical subtypes of PsA:"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"105765",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"1. Oligoarthritis"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"6feaab",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"2. Polyarthritis"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"2e3f51",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"3. DIP-predominant"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ae3bd8",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"4. Arthritis mutilans"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"df155b",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"5. Axial spine involvement"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"0c8b7f",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Enthesitis, dactylitis, and tenosynovitis are commonly seen"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"925b5d",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Pauciarticular large and medium joints; peripheral arthritis can parallel IBD activity"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"8c431e",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Polyarticular peripheral arthritis of small and large joints does not parallel bowel disease; dactylitis; enthesitis"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"843784",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Enthesitis, tenosynovitis and asymmetric large-joint oligoarthritis; usually self-limited and nonerosive; persistent arthritis in up to 25% and may develop MTP erosions"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-2 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"4829c2",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Dermatologic"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"28c8ab",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Psoriatic-like lesions may rarely occur"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"cf1bc9",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Psoriasis typically precedes joint involvement;"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"7eb258",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"nail pitting; onychodystrophy"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"16eebb",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Pyoderma gangrenosum; erythema nodosum"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f9db92",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Keratoderma blennorrhagicum and circinate balanitis (rare)"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-3 row-odd"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"3c4e1f",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Ophthalmologic"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"3c2698",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Anterior uveitis (unilateral, recurrent)"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"6983c5",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Conjunctivitis more common than anterior uveitis"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"93b045",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Anterior uveitis most common; conjunctivitis, keratitis, and episcleritis are rare"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"6983c5",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Conjunctivitis more common than anterior uveitis"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
